<section>
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="feature reveal">
      <p class="eyebrow">Crisis communications</p>
      <h2>Long Island Divided</h2>
      <p>In 2019, Newsday published &ldquo;Long Island Divided,&rdquo; a three-year investigation into housing discrimination across Long Island's real estate industry. I was on the communications team at the Long Island Board of REALTORS&reg; through the difficult public reckoning that followed.</p>
      <p>It remains the clearest lesson of my career in what high-stakes communication actually asks of you: <span class="pull">accuracy over speed, accountability over spin, and steady, honest messaging</span> to members and the public at a moment when saying nothing would have been the easier path.</p>
      <p>That experience is a large part of why I think about a communications role the way your posting describes it: the right message, to the right audience, at the right time, told in a voice people can trust.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

